title: Christmas Carol Collection 2009
creator: Various
description: LibriVox Christmas Carol Collection 2009! The LibriVox community wants to bring you a special treat for the 2009 Holiday Season. Here is a collection of 30 traditional Christmas carols performed in a variety of styles by our wonderful volunteers. Enjoy! For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; christmas; holiday; carols; songs
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: This is super amazing. I just burned a CD with select favorites and will be playing it Christmas Day (and may give it as a gift). Thanks to all who put this together. To make music CD from the MP3's, free software can be downloaded here, and follow instructions here. Stephen

I have not smiled so broadly for so long in at least months and probably years.

My thanks and very best wishes to everyone involved.

Perhaps not all of the recordings are ready for the Albert Hall, but for a collection of free Christmas carols this collection certainly contains some stunningly professional performances. Hey, this is completely free: what do you have to lose?
For this being such a large, yet non-professional collaberative effort I think this is really great. I give this four stars.
